 the Enhancer. Maybe it's too much and not needed actively. Perhaps a more meaningful test could focus solely on the interface class instead. That sounds better! Right now, I might need to create a dedicated test class since I don't have an interface maker file ready. This could streamline the process and help clarify the testing. Let's go for that solution!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_6GeHNVdzCSXPiEGoQXQANlLs|fc_0cab7965373f953a0169ef62c368cc8195a105e7032cd4df42", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/cglib/cglib-nodep/2.2.2/src/test/java/cglib/cglib_nodep/InterfaceMakerTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage cglib.cglib_nodep;\n\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.lang.reflect.Method;\nimport java.util.Arrays;\nimport java.util.List;\nimport java.util.stream.Collectors;\n\nimport net.sf.cglib.proxy.InterfaceMaker;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class InterfaceMakerTest {\n    @Test\n    void createsInterfaceFromPublicClassMethods() throws Exception {\n        InterfaceMaker maker = new InterfaceMaker();\n        maker.add(ExampleOperations.class);\n\n        Class<?> generatedInterface = maker.create();\n\n        List<Method> generatedMethods = Arrays.stream(generatedInterface.getMethods())\n                .filter(method -> method.getDeclaringClass().equals(generatedInterface))\n                .collect(Collectors.toList());\n\n        assertThat(generatedInterface.isInterface()).isTrue();\n        assertThat(generatedMethods)\n                .extracting(Method::getName)\n                .containsExactlyInAnyOrder(\"concat\", \"length\");\n\n        Method concatMethod = generatedInterface.getMethod(\"concat\", String.class, String.class);\n        assertThat(concatMethod.getReturnType()).isEqualTo(String.class);\n        assertThat(concatMethod.getExceptionTypes()).containsExactly(IOException.class);\n    }\n\n    public static class ExampleOperations {\n        public String concat(String left, String right) throws IOException {\n            return left + right;\n        }\n\n        public int length(CharSequence value) {\n            return value.length();\n        }\n\n        protected String protectedMethod() {\n            return \"protected\";\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 652, "output": 1857, "cacheRead": 14336, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 16845, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777296046393, "responseId": "resp_0cab7965373f953a0169ef62aec05c81959572f89b1dee0d1e"}}
